Arlington senior Brandon Keffer placed 21st at the District C-2 race in Norfolk last Thursday to lead the way for the Eagles. Buy Now Tyler Dahlgren 
Sam Anzalone was the second Eagle to cross the finish line at the District C-2 race at Skyview Lake in Norfolk last Thursday. Joe Burns 
Logan Sampson completed the C-2 race at Skyview Lake in Norfolk in 22:43.05 on Thursday. 
Arlington senior Brandon Keffer placed 21 st at Skyview Lake in Norfolk, home of the District C-2 cross country race on Thursday, narrowly missing out on an automatic bid to state. 
Keffer posted a time of 18:55.73 as his stout senior season and Arlington career came to an end. 
“Brandon has had a great season and we had hoped he would qualify but the course wasn't suited very well for his running style,” head coach Sara Horner said. “There was a lot of elevation changes and very little flat ground. 
The next Eagle to come across the finish line was Sam Anzalone in 41 st in 20:13.01. Caleb Hancock was five spots behind him, posting a time of 20:30.66. Cameron Bruning finished in 21:54.80 (56 th ) and Zachary Mann and Logan Sampson were back-to-back in 58 th and 59 th . 
The Eagles came in 10 th , as Columbus Scotus, O'Neill and Columbus Lakeview all qualified for Friday's State Championships in Kearney. 
For the Arlington girls, Lauren Schwedhelm was the only competitor, running a 26:50.77 for 49 th . ×
